14/10/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Following a phone conversation with Pakistani counterpart Shaukat Aziz on Thursday (13 October), Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan said he would visit quake-stricken Pakistan next week. The two leaders discussed assistance Pakistan needs to cope with the disaster. Turkey reportedly will be sending tents and blankets to the devastated areas, while rescue and medical teams already have been dispatched. (Zaman - 14/10/05; Turkishpress.com - 13/10/05)
